ownedComment.body: This class enumerates the three states a timecard can be in.
This class represents a timecard submitted by a person.
TimeAllocation represents a time period for which the timecard submitter worked on the associated task.
A general representation of quanitities of anything. Consists of a value and a unit. For example, 5.00 USD, 10 USD/hour, 100 meters, 100 meters/hour, 100 meters/(hour^2).
This class represents a task for which time allocations need to be tracked.
